    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="603" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d603">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Newberry</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-05-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9,
                            1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 84.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received Mr. Thompson’s No. 76, of 21st
                        ultimo, by which the Department learns with extreme gratification that the
                        Porte has taken action touching censorship of religious books which is
                        satisfactory to the representatives of this missionary interest in
                        Turkey.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
